{"questionId":"27694","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>The function <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>f</mi></math> is defined as&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>f</mi><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mi>ln</mi><mfenced><mrow><mi>x</mi><msup><mtext>e</mtext><mi>x</mi></msup><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfenced><mo>-</mo><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>4</mn></msup></math>, for&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>0</mn><mo>≤</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>≤</mo><mn>2</mn></math>.&nbsp;The graph of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>f</mi></math> is shown&nbsp;in the following diagram.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><img src=\"__IMG__/59cd04b3eea0477c5eab86f9f8655149458d042d.png\"></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:left;\">The graph of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>f</mi></math> has a local maximum at point <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>A</mtext></math>. The graph intersects the <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi></math>-axis at the origin&nbsp;and at point <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>B</mtext></math>.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Find the <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi></math>-coordinate of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>B</mtext></math>.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>1</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>09885</mn><mo>…</mo></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>10</mn></math>&nbsp; accept&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>10</mn><mo>,</mo><mn>0</mn></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em><strong>[1 mark]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"27694","referenceCode":"22N.2.SL.TZ0.3b","subjectId":"50-dp-mathematics-analysis-and-approaches","title":"Find the x-coordinate of B.","paper":"2","level":"SL","questionNumber":"b","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 1]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 2—Functions","Topic 2—Functions","SL 2.4—Key features of graphs, intersections using technology"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}